    {
      "@type": "CreativeWork",
      "name": "The Fantastic Baltic Four: A field sampling approach for four Biology and Ecosystem Essential Ocean Variables (EOVs)",
      "url": "https://zenodo.org/record/19000761",
      "identifier": {
        "@type": "PropertyValue",
        "description": "DOI",
        "propertyID": "https://registry.identifiers.org/registry/doi",
        "url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19000761",
        "value": "10.5281/zenodo.19000761"
      },
      "description": "As part of the EU Horizon project BioEcoOcean, the Baltic Sea Living Lab (BSLL) , implements a novel framework for coastal monitoring around the island of Gotland, Sweden, including the Eastern and Western Gotland Basins. Our research focusses on a set of Biology and Ecosystem Essential Ocean Variables (EOVs) nicknamed the &ldquo;Fantastic Baltic Four&rdquo; (FBF). These are 1) seagrass cover and composition , 2) macroalgal cover and composition , 3) fish abundance and distribution , and 4) benthic invertebrate abundance and distribution . The mission of the BSLL is to provide a holistic understanding of the coastal zone (&lt; 7 m bottom depth) by integrating socio-economic variables, environmental drivers, and ecosystem services such as Blue Foods perspectives. Guided by the 3R principle (Replace, Refine, Reduce) , we aim to minimise the impact of environmental monitoring on marine biota while ensuring scientifically robust observations.",
      "datePublished": "2026-02-24",
      "creator": [
